    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give homeowners rights to compensation if nearby development affects house value",
        "additional_details": "Giving homeowners rights to compensation would make council planners and developers consider the effect on existing homes and ensure the homeowner is compensated when their home is devalued.",
        "background": "Homeowners currently have no recourse if nearby building work or development devalues their property. There should be a process in place where the homeowner can claim the difference between before and after development valuations back from developers.",
